{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/292", "repo": "rails", "body": "Anyways:\r\n\r\n- Users have no idea what KiB is; \r\n- Fitting the file is more important than showing number correctness. \r\n- 90% of users are running Microsoft's products.\r\n\r\nIf you are pragmatic having 1KB = 1000 does not makes sense at this moment when 90% of users still understand 1KB as 1024 bytes.  Ext filesystem does use base 2 as an unit, it just converts before showing it to the user. Let's change the helper, after microsoft changes the way it displays file size numbers.", "_id": {"$oid": "52386324bd3543c15101247e"}, "issue_id": 292, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/1067860", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/292#issuecomment-1067860", "updated_at": "2011-04-28T02:38:27Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eduardordm/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eduardordm/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eduardordm/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eduardordm/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/eduardordm", "login": "eduardordm", "gravatar_id": "9acabffbf83dfcb273626e43b0196937", "html_url": "https://github.com/eduardordm", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eduardordm/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eduardordm/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eduardordm/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/9acabffbf83dfcb273626e43b0196937?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F5bb796fdf326208f007525f5960e175f.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eduardordm/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 473244, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/eduardordm/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2011-04-28T02:38:27Z", "id": 1067860, "owner": "rails"}
